    <section id="troubleshooting">
        <div class="container" style="background-color: #fff;">
            <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

            <h3 class="clickable">Can I add one pixel in the Facebook sales channel Shopify app, and add my other pixels in this app (Pixelfy)?</h3>
            <p id="q1" class="hidden">Also NO, You need to put ALL your pixels into Pixelfy and use ONLY Pixelfy to manage all your pixels. Otherwise you will have duplicates and inaccurate reporting</p>

            <h3 class="clickable">Can I use this app in addition to the Shopify native Facebook pixel integration (in preferences section)?</h3>
            <p id="q2" class="hidden">Also NO, You need to put ALL your pixels into Pixelfy and use ONLY Pixelfy to manage all your pixels. Otherwise you will have duplicates and inaccurate reporting</p>

            <h3 class="clickable" >ill your app slow down my Shopify store?</h3>
            <p id="q3" class="hidden">No, our app is optimized to be fast and uses modern JavaScript, so it will not slow down your store.</p>

            <h3 class="clickable">Will using the app affect my conversion rate on Facebook?</h3>
            <p id="q4" class="hidden">No, using our app will not affect your conversion rate on Facebook. We simply send events and data to Facebook. Additionally, our app supports the iOS 14 update by adding Tokens of Conversion API, which helps improve tracking on iOS devices.</p>

            <h3 class="clickable">How many pixels can I add?</h3>
            <p id="q5" class="hidden">You can add as many pixels as you want. We have no limit on the number of pixels.</p>

            <h3 class="clickable">Does Pixefly support other networks?</h3>
            <p id="q6" class="hidden">Yes, our app supports TikTok, Twitter, and Pinterest in our regular package, and in our premium package, we support Taboola Pixel as well.</p>
            <h3 class="clickable">Do I need to do something before using this app?</h3>
            <p id="q7" class="hidden">Yes, please remove your Facebook Pixel ID from the Facebook sales channel Shopify app, or the Preferences Page on your Shopify Store if you previously added it in there, and remove it from any other pixel tracking app you might have previously used. You will need to use only PIXELFY to manage your Facebook pixels. If you use other tools at the same time, you will have inaccurate reporting
            </p>
            <h3 class="clickable">Do I need to add any code to my theme?</h3>
            <p id="q8" class="hidden">No, you don't need to add any code to your theme</p>
            <h3 class="clickable">What does the collection column mean?</h3>
            <p id="q9" class="hidden">The collection column allows you to choose if you want your pixel to fire for all your store, or fire only for products in a certain collection. If you choose "All - Master / Backup Pixel" for your pixel, then it will fire for all your store. Otherwise if you choose a specific collection, your pixel will fire only for products in that collection, and this will allow to segment your data by niche, and optimize your campaigns more efficiently</p>
            <h3 class="clickable">Is the shipping cost included when reporting the purchase value?</h3>
            <p id="q10" class="hidden">Yes Shipping cost is included in the purchase value in order to allow your Facebook Ads manager to determine the real ROI of your campaigns, and adset</p>
            <h3 class="clickable">How do I check that the app is working properly on my store?</h3>
            <p id="q11" class="hidden">If you would like to check (and we recommed that you do), please use the <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/meta-pixel-helper/fdgfkebogiimcoedlicjlajpkdmockpc" >Facebook pixel helper Chrome browser</a>  extension to check that events are firing correctly on your website</p>
            <h3 class="clickable">Where can I check the events, and values that my Facebook Pixel is reporting?</h3>
            <p id="q12" class="hidden">All events, and values that your pixels send to Facebook will appear in the events manager section of your Facebook business manager. If the events are associated to specific campaigns, they will also appear in your ads manager attributed to their respective campaigns</p>
            <h3 class="clickable">I am a beginner in Facebook advertising. Where can I find my Facebook Pixels ids?</h3>
            <p id="q13" class="hidden">You can get new pixels in your Facebook business manager (you need to create a Facebook business manager if not already created).You can check this link here for guidance >> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/business/help/314143995668266" >https://www.facebook.com/business/help/314143995668266</a></p>
            <h3 class="clickable">I want to cancel my subscription, what do I do?</h3>
